  if (name == null || name.trim().isEmpty()) {
    throw new IllegalArgumentException("Name cannot be empty");
  }

  return GREETING + name + "!";
}
```

This makes the code more robust by avoiding potential NullPointerException.

3. Use StringBuilder for concatenation:

```
public static String greet(String name) {
  StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(GREETING);
  sb.append(name);
  sb.append("!");
  return sb.toString();
}
```

This may improve performance by avoiding repeated string concatenation.

