   public static String greet(String name) {
       if (name == null || name.isEmpty()) {
           return "Hello!";
       }
       return "Hello, " + name + "!";
   }
   ```

   Benefit: Handling null or empty input prevents potential NullPointerExceptions and provides a default greeting when no name is provided.

